document_data.mainbody:
'''Whimberton''' was the chamberlain of [[Castle Lutwill]] and "the ever-glorious and -victorious Baron [[Lutwill]]."
{{Quote|Be silent, or I'll have your backs scourged raw, roll you in rock [[salt]], and heave you into the pigsty for the night.|Whimberton to the gate guards, when they were arguing about whether he wanted to hear a ribald tale about a [[firbolg]] and a [[halfling]].}}
